{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778173527,"nonce":"y4Sh7NHL0HGE15TqyWqfnlLagis=","message":"**Δv metric correction (clarification, not a result change).**\n\n`compute_velocity_inflation`'s headline scalar `delta_v_percent` was based on peak *speed* (2-norm of velocity); it has now been corrected to peak *forward velocity* — signed projection onto the reach axis — matching C\u0026S 2019 (p. 8137 Statistical design; Fig 1e; Results p. 8139). Peak lateral velocity is now also exposed via `delta_v_lateral_percent` for the orthogonal channel.\n\n**Numerical impact on prior Δv results: nil.** Every existing velocity-inflation test uses an on-axis unperturbed reach (target along x, no disturbance). For these inputs, lateral velocity is identically zero and peak speed = peak forward velocity by symmetry. Re-running reproduces the prior table exactly:\n\n| Regime | Δv (peak speed, prior) | Δv (peak forward, post-fix) |\n|---|---|---|\n| rlrmp k=10, 1.5γ* | +5.44% | +5.44% |\n| rlrmp k=10, 1.05γ* | +12.82% | +12.82% |\n| C\u0026S plant, rlrmp Q,R | −0.77% | −0.77% |\n| C\u0026S plant, faithful Eq. 15 Q,R | −0.04% (xfail) | −0.04% (xfail) |\n\n**Why this matters going forward.** Future Δv work — perturbed rollouts, off-axis reaches, the induced-gain analyser (`74bfd86`) — *will* exercise the metric distinction (lateral motion present, two-channel signature). The fix is infrastructure for those analyses, not a re-interpretation of past results.\n\n**Impact on flavor (a) ⊊ (b) interpretation:** strengthened. The C\u0026S-regime −0.04% is on the *unperturbed forward* channel — the channel where C\u0026S explicitly say robust \u003e LQG by virtue of higher feedback gains alone (no disturbance needed). Our flavor-(a) H∞ collapses to LQR on this channel, confirming that the gain inflation C\u0026S report depends on flavor-(b) `ΔA·x` model uncertainty (cross-ref `c99ad9d` thread on the original finding; mechanistic fix tracked at `97c227a`).\n\nIssue: `f90bf74`. Auth request: `420a122c`.","files":null}]}